 Four suspects appeared in Middelburg Regional Court on charges of fraud, theft and money laundering on Wednesday. ALSO READ:Court cancels sale of Big Joe’s possessions Provincial Hawks spokesman, Capt Lucy Dineo Sekgotodi said that Linda Ebersohn (56), Frans Hendrik Ebersohn (58), Francios Ebersohn (31) and Hendrik Stepheneous Eberson (25) were detained on Tuesday. “The four family members were arrested for alleged fraud amounting to R 12 million. It is alleged that in 2017 Linda, who was employed by Middelburg Dakkappe company as a debtor and credit clerk, allegedly defrauded the establishment by sending funds into her personal accounts and to family members. ALSO READ:Accused in murders of elderly women appear in court It is also alleged that several fake creditors accounts and existing creditor particulars were also utilised,” he said. They were remanded in custody and the case was postponed to December 3.